      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 7-year-old boy is brought to the pediatric clinic with a history of yellowing skin and eyes. Laboratory tests reveal increased levels of serum bilirubin and bilirubin in the urine, but urobilinogen is not detected. Based on these findings, what is the most likely diagnosis?</span></span></span></p>",
